cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with analyzing crowd behavior from video data, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper proposes a model to capture the spatio-temporal interaction pattern of the crowd, which can be seen as a social network of individuals. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an unsupervised approach to analyze crowd behavior, which involves learning patterns and features from the data. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with analyzing crowd behavior from video data, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper proposes an effective group detection algorithm that utilizes the eigenvectors of the interaction matrix of the model, which can be seen as a human-computer interaction problem.
